  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-10">
    <div class="mb-6">
      <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 bg-primary-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Guides</span>
      <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400 ml-3">Updated March 2026</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">How to Read Electric Meter in Pakistan — Complete Guide</h1>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-8 text-lg leading-relaxed">Understanding your electricity meter helps you track consumption and avoid bill shock. Pakistan uses both analog disc meters and modern digital/smart meters. This guide explains how to read both types and how your meter reading translates to your monthly bill.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to read a digital electricity meter in Pakistan?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">A digital meter shows units consumed as a number (e.g., 1234 kWh). Note the reading at the start and end of the month. The difference is your consumption. DISCO meter readers record this number when they visit monthly.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to read an analog electricity meter?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Read the dials from right to left. Each dial moves when the one to its right completes a full rotation. If a pointer is between two numbers, record the lower number. Ignore the last red dial. Subtract previous reading from current to get units consumed.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Why is my meter reading different from my bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">If your meter reading differs from your bill, it may be an estimated bill (DISCO estimated your consumption instead of physically reading the meter). You can contest estimated bills by calling DISCO helpline 118 and providing your actual meter photo.</div></details>
    </div>

